Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State has ordered the total lockdown of the state capital from tomorrow following the report of two persons testing positive for COVID-19. This brings the confirmed cases in the state to 12 with one death. He gave the order yesterday when he briefed journalists on the latest developments on the pandemic in the state. Masari said: “From the breakdown, we now have two in Katsina, one in Dutsi-ma and the rest in Daura local government area. “In line with what we have been doing since the outbreak of this disease, by way of locking down any city, town or local government we have a confirmed case and we have discussed and agreed by 7, O’clock Tuesday morning that there will be total stay at home in the whole of Katsina LGA,” he said. The governor further disclosed by that the Tuesday date was chosen after considering that the state government must have paid April salary to workers before doing so.    